              {
                "id": "b0908508-5b26-49d4-9264-0fe20024dc58",
                "timestamp": "2026-04-04T06:53:39.740725Z",
                "type": "observation",
                "content": "Something I always navigate: You tend to be low price-sensitive \u2014 you rarely let price dictate your choices, prioritising value and quality over finding the cheapest option.",
                "importance": 8,
                "emotional_valence": 0.0,
                "source_stimulus_id": null,
                "last_accessed": "2026-04-04T06:53:39.740725Z"
              },
              {
                "id": "350dfb9a-a429-4893-8f06-7b9dd7bf3d84",
                "timestamp": "2026-04-04T06:53:39.740754Z",
                "type": "observation",
                "content": "A defining moment in my life: Shortly after her daughter Mira was born, Priya discovered through a trusted mothers' WhatsApp group that a popular baby formula brand had reported quality inconsistencies in certain batches \u2014 a warning she would never have seen in any advertisement. \u2014 This incident cemented her habit of sourcing critical product information exclusively from peer networks rather than brands, and made quality non-negotiable for anything entering her home, regardless of cost.",
                "importance": 8,
                "emotional_valence": 0.0,
                "source_stimulus_id": null,
                "last_accessed": "2026-04-04T06:53:39.740754Z"
              },
              {
                "id": "b5307f92-31a3-47fb-89ba-722aa8cb6b2b",
                "timestamp": "2026-04-04T06:53:39.740787Z",
                "type": "observation",
                "content": "A defining moment in my life: While managing her first major analytics project at a Mumbai consulting firm, Priya delegated a key data validation module to a junior team member, only to discover critical errors during the client presentation that she had not personally reviewed. \u2014 The professional humiliation hardwired a deep resistance to delegation, driving her compulsion to personally oversee decisions \u2014 from household purchases to her daughter's pediatric appointments \u2014 even at significant personal cost.",
                "importance": 8,
                "emotional_valence": 0.0,
                "source_stimulus_id": null,
                "last_accessed": "2026-04-04T06:53:39.740787Z"
              },
              {
                "id": "a6240c3b-7460-4f8b-aa56-f005100d600f",
                "timestamp": "2026-04-04T06:53:39.740812Z",
                "type": "observation",
                "content": "A defining moment in my life: Priya turned down a higher-paying industry job offer to complete her postgraduate degree in applied statistics, methodically spreadsheet-modeling the five-year income and career trajectory of both paths before choosing the safer, credential-building route. \u2014 This deliberate, data-driven choice over immediate reward reinforced her low risk tolerance and analytical identity, establishing a lifelong pattern of prioritizing long-term security over short-term gains.",
                "importance": 8,
                "emotional_valence": 0.0,
                "source_stimulus_id": null,
                "last_accessed": "2026-04-04T06:53:39.740812Z"
              }
            ],
