            "title": "The Research Thesis That Rewrote Her Standards",
            "when": "age 26",
            "event": "While completing her postgraduate thesis in biochemistry at Cochin University, she discovered a critical methodological error in a peer-reviewed paper she had cited \u2014 an error that nearly invalidated six months of her own work. She spent three sleepless weeks reconstructing her data pipeline from scratch, alone, refusing her supervisor's offer to co-author a correction.",
            "lasting_impact": "This episode cemented her distrust of delegated work and external validation; she now verifies everything herself and defaults to trusting her own judgment over any institutional or peer authority."
          },
          {
            "title": "The Mutual Fund Collapse She Saw Coming",
            "when": "age 34",
            "event": "After a colleague enthusiastically invested their joint office group fund into an aggressive mid-cap scheme in 2013, the portfolio lost 38% within eighteen months \u2014 exactly the scenario she had flagged in a written note to the group that was ignored. She had quietly kept her own savings in fixed deposits.",
            "lasting_impact": "The experience locked in a deeply conservative financial posture; she maintains a risk tolerance well below her income bracket and feels visceral discomfort whenever family finances deviate from predictable, controlled instruments."
          },
          {
            "title": "The Morning Walk That Became Architecture",
            "when": "age 38",
            "event": "After her younger child started school full-time, she committed to a 5:45 AM walk along Marine Drive every single day for ninety days as a structured experiment in reclaiming personal time \u2014 she logged it in a spreadsheet and almost never missed a day regardless of weather or social obligations.",
            "lasting_impact": "The experiment revealed how profoundly she is wired by repetition and structure; she now organizes nearly every domain of her life \u2014 meals, work blocks, purchases \u2014 around non-negotiable routines, explaining her exceptionally high habit strength and indifference to spontaneous social plans."
          }
