                "age_when": 28,
                "event": "A junior team member submitted an error-riddled financial audit to a client under her name, causing the firm to lose a major account and triggering a senior review of her work. She spent three weeks personally reconstructing every dataset to prove the error was not systemic.",
                "lasting_impact": "Instilled a near-permanent distrust of delegating critical tasks, cementing her belief that quality is only guaranteed when she controls the output herself \u2014 a tension she still navigates daily."
              },
              {
                "age_when": 29,
                "event": "She invested a significant portion of her early savings into a technology-sector mutual fund on a colleague's recommendation, only to watch it lose 60% of its value within eight months during the dot-com bust.",
                "lasting_impact": "This single loss recalibrated her entire financial worldview toward low-risk, self-researched instruments, making her deeply skeptical of peer-driven financial advice and anchoring her low risk tolerance to this day."
              },
              {
                "age_when": 41,
                "event": "Her mother was admitted to a Chennai corporate hospital for what turned out to be a manageable condition, but aggressive diagnostic protocols and poor communication from attending doctors led to a two-week stay and a bill that felt disproportionate to the actual medical need.",
