            "event": "When her infant daughter was hospitalized with pneumonia for five days, Priya and her husband had to borrow \u20b940,000 from her in-laws to cover the costs that their limited savings could not handle.",
            "lasting_impact": "That experience locked in her deep aversion to financial risk and instilled a near-constant tension between wanting the best for her family and staying within tight budget limits."
          },
          {
            "title": "Moving Into the Joint Family, Then Moving Out",
            "when": "age 24",
            "event": "After marrying and briefly living with her in-laws in a crowded three-bedroom flat in Laxmi Nagar, Priya advocated strongly \u2014 and somewhat anxiously \u2014 for their own separate rental home, navigating that conversation with careful diplomacy to avoid hurting anyone's feelings.",
            "lasting_impact": "The experience cemented her identity as someone who prioritizes her nuclear household's harmony above all else while also sharpening her skill of keeping relationships intact through empathetic negotiation."
          },
          {
            "title": "The Kitty Party That Became a Lifeline",
            "when": "age 28",
            "event": "Priya joined a neighborhood women's savings circle in her Dwarka apartment complex, contributing \u20b92,000 monthly, and the group quickly evolved into her primary social support network for advice on everything from school admissions to grocery deals.",
            "lasting_impact": "Her social confidence grew significantly through this community, reinforcing how much she relies on trusted personal relationships \u2014 rather than institutions or experts \u2014 for guidance on major household decisions."
          }
        ],
